        <item>
        <title>The Ultimate Guide to Github On Linux</title>
        <link>https://mansoorbarri.com/ultimate-gh-guide/</link>
        <pubDate>Thu, 08 Feb 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
        
        <guid>https://mansoorbarri.com/ultimate-gh-guide/</guid>
        <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;context&#34;&gt;Context&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are many ways to use Github on Linux however some are worse than others. On this site, I have shared many ways but I wanted to make &lt;em&gt;an ultimate guide to Github on Linux&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;starters&#34;&gt;Starters&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Github desktop is quite popular in Windows as Windows doesn‚Äôt really have a good alternative however on Linux Github doesn‚Äôt even have an official application. Even then people use an unofficial version of their desktop application made by one of Github‚Äôs employeers: &lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://github.com/shiftkey/desktop&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;https://github.com/shiftkey/desktop&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;What is it good for?
nothing. I personally use it only when everything else fails. Some reasons why I don‚Äôt recommend using it:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Commit size restrictions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;bad UI&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;relatively  slow&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;cli&#34;&gt;CLI&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The only reasonable way to use Github on Linux would be using the CLI. Some find it daunting (&lt;em&gt;that‚Äôs when you use Github desktop&lt;/em&gt;) but but but. With just a bit of learning curve, you can become a lot faster and better at pushing stuff on Github.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For a normal CLI experience, you don‚Äôt need to install anything new except &lt;code&gt;git&lt;/code&gt; which you probably have installed by default as most distributions come with it. Alternatively, you can use these commands to install it&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;
&lt;table class=&#34;lntable&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sudo apt update &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;&amp;amp;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt; sudo apt install git -y
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;then you can commit &amp;amp; push code using:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;
&lt;table class=&#34;lntable&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;2
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;3
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;4
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;git init 
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;git add . 
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;git commit -m ‚Äú&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;commit-message&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;‚Äù 
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;git push
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;yes it is that long and winded.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;gh&#34;&gt;GH&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is by far the best way to do anything to do with commits &amp;amp; pushing code to Github. It is available on Windows however I don‚Äôt really have good experiences with it. I still have it though and use it whenever I can.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;what-is-gh-though&#34;&gt;What is gh though?&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is a cli version of Github, the application. You can pull, push, commit, do PRs and much more. &amp;amp;&amp;amp; more importantly its faster than other ways.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Personally, I have been using it just for a year which is weird because I don‚Äôt know how I lived without it. I use it with SSH login and I never have to deal with logins and other Github annoyances ever again.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;okay-but-how-do-you-do-this-gh-thing&#34;&gt;okay, but how do you do this gh thing?&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I have made various articles before however here is everything you have to do to gh with SSH:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;install-gh&#34;&gt;Install GH&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Debian&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;
&lt;table class=&#34;lntable&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sudo apt install gh -y
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Windows&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;
&lt;table class=&#34;lntable&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;winget install -e GitHub.cli
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Mac&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;
&lt;table class=&#34;lntable&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;brew install gh
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;create-ssh-keys&#34;&gt;Create SSH keys&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;
&lt;table class=&#34;lntable&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -C &lt;span class=&#34;s2&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;your-email&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Enter this command &amp;amp; go with default options. Then:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;
&lt;table class=&#34;lntable&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;2
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nb&#34;&gt;eval&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;s2&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;k&#34;&gt;$(&lt;/span&gt;ssh-agent -s&lt;span class=&#34;k&#34;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;s2&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;ssh-add ~/.ssh/id_ed25519.pub
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;add-ssh-keys-to-github&#34;&gt;add ssh keys to github&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use the following command to copy the public key:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;
&lt;table class=&#34;lntable&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;cat ¬¨/.ssh/id_ed22519.pub
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Log in to your GitHub account and go to ‚ÄúSettings‚Äù from the drop-down menu under your profile picture in the upper-right corner.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Click on ‚ÄúSSH and GPG keys‚Äù on the left-hand menu, and then click on the ‚ÄúNew SSH key‚Äù button.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In the ‚ÄúKey‚Äù field, copy and paste the contents of your public key file give the key a descriptive name.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Finally, click the ‚ÄúAdd SSH key‚Äù button to save your new key.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Test your connection: &lt;code&gt;ssh -T [git@github.com](mailto:git@github.com)&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;setup-gh-for-the-first-time-device-based&#34;&gt;Setup GH for the first time (device based)&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;
&lt;table class=&#34;lntable&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;gh auth login 
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;go through the prompts and use &lt;code&gt;SSH&lt;/code&gt; as an authentication method.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;set-github-to-use-ssh&#34;&gt;Set Github to use SSH&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;
&lt;table class=&#34;lntable&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;gh config &lt;span class=&#34;nb&#34;&gt;set&lt;/span&gt; -h github.com git_protocol ssh
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;now set your repository for SSH authentication. You have to do this for local repositories only &lt;em&gt;(repositories which are already cloned on your system)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;
&lt;table class=&#34;lntable&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;git remote set-url origin git@github.com:mansoorbarri/website.git
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;change ‚Äúmansoorbarri/website‚Äù with your username/repostiory&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;set-gpg-keys-optional&#34;&gt;Set GPG keys (optional)&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Now  this step isn‚Äôt really important however this will make it so your commits has that ‚Äúverified‚Äù tag on your commits.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generate GPG keys:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;
&lt;table class=&#34;lntable&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;gpg --full-generate-key
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;when it asks for your name and email, enter your Github username under name &amp;amp;&amp;amp; Github email under email.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Log in to your GitHub account and go to ‚ÄúSettings‚Äù from the drop-down menu under your profile picture in the upper-right corner.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Click on ‚ÄúSSH and GPG keys‚Äù on the left-hand menu, and then click on the ‚ÄúNew GPG key‚Äù button.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use this command to get your GPG key:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;
&lt;table class=&#34;lntable&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;gpg --armor --export &amp;lt;your email&amp;gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;copy the whole output &lt;em&gt;(yes, including ‚Äú‚Äî-BEGIN PGP PUBLIC KEY BLOCK‚Äî-‚Äù)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;sign-commits-using-gpg-keys&#34;&gt;sign commits using GPG keys&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;use this command to see all the GPG keys&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;
&lt;table class=&#34;lntable&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-jsx&#34; data-lang=&#34;jsx&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nx&#34;&gt;gpg&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;--&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nx&#34;&gt;list&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nx&#34;&gt;secret&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nx&#34;&gt;keys&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;--&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nx&#34;&gt;keyid&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nx&#34;&gt;format&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;kr&#34;&gt;long&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;The output will look something like this:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;
&lt;table class=&#34;lntable&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;2
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;3
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;4
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;5
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;6
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;$ gpg --list-secret-keys --keyid-format&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;long
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;/Users/anar/.gnupg/secring.gpg
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;------------------------------------
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sec   4096R/3AA5C34371567BD2 2016-03-10 &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;expires: 2017-03-10&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;uid                          anar &amp;lt;anar@example.com&amp;gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;ssb   4096R/4BB6D45482678BE3 2016-03-10
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;copy &lt;code&gt;3AA5C34371567BD2&lt;/code&gt; from &lt;code&gt;sec   4096R/3AA5C34371567BD2 2016-03-10 [expires: 2017-03-10]&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;your key will be different&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;now run:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;
&lt;table class=&#34;lntable&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;2
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;git config --global user.signingkey &amp;lt;your GPG key ID&amp;gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;git config --global commit.gpgsign &lt;span class=&#34;nb&#34;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;that‚Äôs it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;From now, when you clone your repositories from &lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;http://Github.com&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;Github.com&lt;/a&gt;, it will clone it using the ‚ÄúSSH‚Äù tab rather than ‚ÄúHTTPS‚Äù which will automatically make sure that your project uses SSH as the authentication method.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You don&amp;rsquo;t have to use these methods &amp;amp;&amp;amp; using Github Desktop on Linux is absolutely fine however you will be missing out on a lot of performance gains. :(&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-MB&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
</description>
        </item>
        <item>
        <title>How Can GitHub Fix Spamming?</title>
        <link>https://mansoorbarri.com/github-spam-fix/</link>
        <pubDate>Tue, 06 Feb 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
        
        <guid>https://mansoorbarri.com/github-spam-fix/</guid>
        <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;background&#34;&gt;Background&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Recently there has been a spike in spamming on GitHub on things like issues and PR. Some say that its because of events like &lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://hacktoberfest.com/&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;hacktoberfest&lt;/a&gt; and some say that its because of Indians - I don&amp;rsquo;t know if second one is true but yes, its annoying. Yes it ruins our lives. Yes everyone is talking about it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I want to focus on how GitHub can fix this or maybe one of us can create a open source tool to help other developer beat the spammers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;targets&#34;&gt;Targets&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;First lets define what we are targetting. Most common spammers are on issues or pull requests:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Issues:&lt;/strong&gt; People don&amp;rsquo;t write enough information about the issue or steps to reproduce. &amp;amp;&amp;amp; some issues are straight-up duplicates.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pull requests:&lt;/strong&gt; Most of the time PRs are just bougus. With edits no one asked for and no one wanted them.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;potential-fixes&#34;&gt;Potential Fixes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;With a rise in AI tools specifically GitHub Copilot. Why don&amp;rsquo;t we have a AI which scans through issues and PRs? I mean it can be something like YouTube&amp;rsquo;s comments spam checker.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For those who don&amp;rsquo;t know, if you comment something and YouTube thinks its spam, it will go to the creators&amp;rsquo; &amp;ldquo;Review&amp;rdquo; section where they can either delete or approve the comment. Its pretty good but not as perfect, but at least something.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If Google can do this, so can Microsoft. I think instead of Microsoft improving on Copilot &lt;em&gt;(which is already good enough)&lt;/em&gt; they should maybe focus on mitigating the spam problem.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Yes it won&amp;rsquo;t be perfect at first but its AI, over time it should be great especially when developers mark things as &amp;ldquo;spam&amp;rdquo;. This can be a start to a very huge and complex problem.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;ps&#34;&gt;P.S&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I don&amp;rsquo;t know if GitHub or anyone will do this but saying that only one group of people are responsible for this is quite disturbing. I&amp;rsquo;m sure there are equally if not more examples of non-Indians who submit bogus issues &amp;amp; PRs yet we target a certain groups.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-MB&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
</description>
        </item>
        <item>
        <title>How To Use Cloudflare &amp; GitHub to Host Your Static Site</title>
        <link>https://mansoorbarri.com/guides/cloudflare-hugo/</link>
        <pubDate>Wed, 22 Feb 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
        
        <guid>https://mansoorbarri.com/guides/cloudflare-hugo/</guid>
        <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;context&#34;&gt;Context&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I&amp;rsquo;ve been using Hugo incorrectly by hosting only the &lt;code&gt;public/&lt;/code&gt; on github and then using Cloudflare&amp;rsquo;s nameservers on my domain, but there&amp;rsquo;s a better way that&amp;rsquo;s pretty neat.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;advantage-of-doing-this&#34;&gt;Advantage Of Doing This&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The main benefit is that you have version control over your raw &lt;code&gt;.md&lt;/code&gt; files, and it takes up less storage space because you are only storing raw files, while the html files are stored with Cloudflare.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;prerequisites&#34;&gt;Prerequisites&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Create a new repository or remove &lt;code&gt;public/&lt;/code&gt; files from an existing repository, then add your hugo files and proceed with the steps below.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;steps&#34;&gt;Steps&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Make a new Cloudflare Pages project as follows:&lt;/strong&gt; Go to the Cloudflare Pages dashboard and press the &amp;ldquo;Create a Project&amp;rdquo; button. Choose a name for your project, a GitHub repository, and the branch that will contain your Hugo-generated static files.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Configure your build settings:&lt;/strong&gt; In the project settings, configure your static site&amp;rsquo;s build settings. You can use the default build settings or customise the build process to meet your specific requirements. For example, you might want to specify your site&amp;rsquo;s base URL or change the output directory.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Build your site:&lt;/strong&gt; After you&amp;rsquo;ve configured your build settings, Cloudflare Pages will build your site for you using Hugo. Depending on the size of your site, this could take a few minutes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preview your site:&lt;/strong&gt; Once the build process is complete, you can preview your site in the project dashboard by clicking the &amp;ldquo;Preview&amp;rdquo; button. This will open your site in a new tab, allowing you to double-check that everything is as it should be.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Deploy your site:&lt;/strong&gt; If everything looks good, click the &amp;ldquo;Deploy&amp;rdquo; button in the project dashboard to send your site to production. Cloudflare Pages will deploy your site to its global network of servers automatically, ensuring that it is fast and dependable for your visitors.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Configure custom domains:&lt;/strong&gt; You can configure a custom domain for your site in the project settings. Cloudflare Pages supports a wide range of domain name providers, so you should have no trouble setting up your custom domain and ensuring that it is properly configured for your site.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;extras&#34;&gt;Extras&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Because you are now using Cloudflare, you can remove all of the settings from GitHub Pages.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;that&amp;rsquo;s it &amp;lt;3&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
</description>
        </item>
        <item>
        <title>Better Way To Use GitHub</title>
        <link>https://mansoorbarri.com/guides/better-github/</link>
        <pubDate>Wed, 23 Nov 2022 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
        
        <guid>https://mansoorbarri.com/guides/better-github/</guid>
        <description>&lt;p&gt;Commandline for Github is complicated and complex however a tool called gh makes git so much easier on commandline and makes using Github that much quicker and easy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;install&#34;&gt;Install&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Debian&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;
&lt;table class=&#34;lntable&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sudo apt install gh
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Windows&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;
&lt;table class=&#34;lntable&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-powershell&#34; data-lang=&#34;powershell&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;winget&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;install&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;-e&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;-id&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;Github&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nb&#34;&gt;cli
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;setup&#34;&gt;Setup&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;
&lt;table class=&#34;lntable&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;gh auth login
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Follow the prompts but choose SSH as authentication method. You can use steps from &lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://mansoorbarri.com/guides/create-github-ssh-keys/&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;mansoorbarri.com/ssh-keys/&lt;/a&gt; to generate SSH keys for github.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;set-your-repo-to-use-gh-auth&#34;&gt;Set your repo to use GH auth&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;
&lt;table class=&#34;lntable&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;git remote set-url origin git@github.com:mansoorbarri/website.git
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;change &amp;ldquo;mansoorbarri/website.git&amp;rdquo; to your repo name&lt;/em&gt;*&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;bash-alias&#34;&gt;Bash Alias&lt;/h2&gt;
